{
    "text": "Known as the \u201cPatagonia of the North\u201d, Tombstone Territorial Park is 2,200 squared kilometers of pristine wilderness with picturesque rugged peaks, permafrost landforms, and a wide array of unique flora and fauna.  \u2063 There are plenty of hiking trails and campsites - from easy beginner trails like the North Klondike River trail or Goldensides to back country overnight trips like Grizzly, Talus, or Divide Lake. \u2063 One of the best times to visit is during late summer when the tundra vegetation paints the landscape in vivid crimson, gold and red. Would you go explore this vast wilderness?\u2063 \u2063 Follow @naturefandom \ud83d\ude4c Follow @naturefandom \ud83d\ude4c  \ud83d\udccc Yukon, Canada \ud83c\udde8\ud83c\udde6\u2063\u2063\u2063\u2063\u2063\u2063\u2063\u2063\u2063 \u2063 \ud83d\udcf8 Thank you @juliuathompson @chrisrlocke @thismattexists @anatoletuzlak @rammy.photo @tayuhayward and @timsphotos for your great pics!\u2063 \u2063. . . . #yukon #yukonterritory #canadalove #canada\ud83c\udde8\ud83c\udde6 #wildernessculture #wilderness #wild #canada #canadatravel #naturefandom #landscapes #landscape_lovers #landscape_photography #placestovisit #hikingculture #hiking #hike #hikemoreworryless #natureheals #naturephotographer  #hiketheworld #exploretheworld",
